# Download and install Jython on Windows:

Step 1: Go to this link to download Jython

		https://jython.org/downloads.html


Step 2: Click the below download option to download Jython

		Download Jython 2.7.0 - Installer: Executable jar for installing Jython


Step 3: After downloading, double click on the jar file to install Jython


Step 4: After installing, set the Jython path in environmental variables

		Under System variables,

		JYTHON_HOME : C:\jython2.7.0
		Path : %JYTHON_HOME%\bin


Step 5: Open command prompt and type
	
		jython

		Jython interpreter starts...




# To import jar file in Jython:

>>> import sys
>>> sys.path.append("E:\Anisha\Downloads\helloworld.jar")
>>> import helloworld